text.headline: Hundred Years' War
text.text:
24 May 1337 – 19 October 1453

(116 years, 4 months, 3 weeks and 4 days)

text.headline: Rollo the Viking, first ruler of Normandy
text.text: Rollo (c. 860 – c. 930 ) was a Viking who became the first ruler of Normandy. Charles the Simple, the king of West Francia, ceded lands between the mouth of the Seine and what is now Rouen in exchange for Rollo agreeing to end his brigandage, and provide the Franks with protection against future Viking raids.

media.caption: Rollo on the Statue of William the Conqueror in Falaise town square
